NOMURA SECURITIES INTERNATIONAL, INC. Revenue and Financial Data


   Nomura Securities International has its eye on fixed income. The US-based unit of top Japanese brokerage Nomura Holdings provides securities research and trading, asset management, and capital markets services. The company caters to individual, institutional, corporate, and government clients. Nomura Securities International is a leading seller of Japanese equities in the US. The company's fixed income division underwrites and trades government bonds and derivatives. It ceased trading mortgage-related securities in 2007. Nomura Securities International opened its first US office in New York in 1927, and has extended its reach to all of North and South America.
  







