Capital Markets

Company Overview of Nomura Securities International, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Nomura Securities International, Inc. offers arbitrage securities brokerage services. It trades mortgaged-backed securities, structured financial securities, and equities. The company underwrites and trades government bonds and derivatives. It also provides asset management and investment banking services. The company operates businesses in four primary areas such as fixed income, equities, investment banking, and asset management. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in New York, New York with branch offices in Los Angeles, San Francisco, California; Honolulu, Hawaii; and Chicago, Illinois. Nomura Securities International, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Nomura Holding America, Inc...
Nomura Securities International, Inc. offers arbitrage securities brokerage services. It trades mortgaged-backed securities, structured financial securities, and equities. The company underwrites and trades government bonds and derivatives. It also provides asset management and investment banking services. The company operates businesses in four primary areas such as fixed income, equities, investment banking, and asset management. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in New York, New York with branch offices in Los Angeles, San Francisco, California; Honolulu, Hawaii; and Chicago, Illinois. Nomura Securities International, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Nomura Holding America, Inc.
